item.value: Ensure that a release propagates, even if there are other in-progress acquiresreleases. This proceeds in the usual way of trying to unparkSuccessor of head if it needs signal. But if it does not, status is set to PROPAGATE to ensure that upon release, propagation continues. Additionally, we must loop in case a new node is added while we are doing this. Also, unlike other uses of unparkSuccessor, we need to know if CAS to reset status fails, if so rechecking.
Thread to unpark is held in successor, which is normally just the next node. But if cancelled or apparently null, traverse backwards from tail to find the actual non-cancelled successor.
If status is negative (i.e., possibly needing signal) try to clear in anticipation of signalling. It is OK if this fails or if status is changed by waiting thread.
